# 🛒 E-commerce Purchase Prediction

## 📌 Project Overview
This machine learning project predicts whether a customer will generate revenue on an e-commerce platform based on their behavior data.
The project demonstrates a complete ML workflow including preprocessing, model building, evaluation, and hyperparameter tuning.

## 🚀 Problem Statement
Given customer activity data, predict whether the customer will make a purchase (Revenue = 1) or not (Revenue = 0).

## 📊 Dataset Information
- Features include customer behavior and session data
- Target variable: Revenue
  - 1 → Customer made a purchase
  - 0 → Customer did not make a purchase

## ⚙️ Workflow

1. Data Loading
2. Data Preprocessing
   - Handling categorical variables
   - Scaling numerical features
3. Train-Test Split (Stratified)
4. Model Building
   - Decision Tree Classifier
5. Pipeline Creation
6. Model Evaluation
   - Confusion Matrix
   - Classification Report
   - F1 Score
7. Hyperparameter Tuning using GridSearchCV
8. Cross Validation

## 🧠 Model Used
- Decision Tree Classifier

